Description:
Style Meets Character In Fantastic Locale
Beautiful presentation and innovative design has transformed this two bedroom Californian Bungalow into something truly special.
Timber floors line a spacious living and study domain, leading through the hall way which offers two bedrooms with central bathroom, the master featuring a split system heating/cooling and BIRs, along with a foldable staircase leading to roof storage space.
Featuring a well-equipped kitchen with granite benchtops, Smeg appliances including a 900mm oven and gas cooktop, and myrtle timber cupboards with ample storage space. This leads into the dining/family room and undercover decking area, perfect for indoor/outdoor entertaining. There is also off street parking for two cars along with a full side drive leading to a garage/shed area, spilt system heating/cooling in both living areas, an open fireplace, solar panels and well-manicured gardens.
All within close proximity to Coburg North shopping precinct, Batman & Coburg Railway Stations, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafés, Farmer's Market and the Merri Creek bike trail.
Insights: 3 A'beckett Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Once in a Lifetime...
"LYNDON" - occupying a substantial high-side allotment in the prestigious Glencairn Estate, this attractive Californian Bungalow provides an immediately comfortable family lifestyle along with outstanding options to enhance and expand in the future (STCA). Enjoyed and immaculately maintained by the one family for many decades, the home's previously extended interior showcases a wonderfully wide central hallway, four generous bedrooms and two bathrooms. Formal and informal living zones include a front lounge and adjoining dining room, spotless/kitchen meals through to the light-filled open living/dining area. Impressively high ceilings throughout with distinctive Art Deco plasterwork, the home also includes gas heating and a large laundry complete with original copper boiler. Step outside to discover a sizeable north-facing backyard with studio/storeroom, garage/workshop via gated side driveway and ROW at the rear. Walking distance to local parks and primary schools (Brunswick North and St Fidelis), John Fawkner medical precinct, Moreland Road buses and Moreland Station, it's also close to cafes and shops, as well as easy access to Citylink.

Description:
Options Aplenty
Set on approximately 600m2 of prime real estate in a highly sought after tree-lined location this Californian Bungalow with rear ROW access will impress the most discerning of owner occupiers, investors and developers (subject to council approval). Within easy access to everything that Coburg has to offer, this golden opportunity will reward an array of buyers with its amazing potential. Offering a living room with window seat, kitchen/meals with electric cooking facilities and backyard, the home presently features high ceilings, elaborate rosettes, a gas heater, polished floorboards and slate flooring. Double bedrooms, including one hosting a mirrored built-in robe with concealed desk, share a bathroom and there's also a laundry. Parking is taken care of by a side driveway, leading to a garage. A stroll to Coburg Railway Station, trams, buses, Merri Creek Trail, schools, Sydney Road and Coburg Market it is a unique opportunity.

Description:
Classic Coburg With Cosmopolitan Heart
Fall in love with this freestanding two bedroom home that beats with a cosmopolitan heart close to cafes, Sydney Road shops and eateries, Coburg market, schools, Coburg and Batman train stations, trams, bike paths and CBD access. Ready to be returned to former glory, the residence displays classic period appeal with ceilings that reach to over three metres in height! Featuring coveted rear right-of-way access and a garage, the residence offers generously proportioned bedrooms, spacious kitchen/meals/lounge area, cute sunroom/study, central bathroom with corner shower, a fully sized laundry, plus undercover alfresco entertaining area in level, fenced rear yard. In fine condition as is and well tenanted, there is also brilliant scope to revamp/restyle/restore/extend (STCA) and reap the rewards. Extras include ceiling fans, split system, a built-in-robe, two sheds and external security shutters. With everything in place for a brilliant makeover it will be a breeze to rejuvenate and capitalise on the existing charm of this delightful home.

Large, Light-filled and Refurbished
Get set for something special with this larger than normal tri-level three bedroom two bathroom contemporary townhouse, where quality finishes, huge bedrooms and an array of balconies makes it a standout. Boasting a fashionable Pentridge Village address, within approximately 10km to the Melbourne CBD this executive lifestyle can be yours. Relaxing living spaces fuse with a granite topped kitchen featuring glass splashback and a suite of stainless steel appliances. Two impressively sized bedrooms include master with ensuite, and a spacious family bathroom preside over the top floor, while a huge ground floor bedroom with exterior access presents versatility. Stroll to cafes, restaurants, Coburg Railway Station, trams, Lake Reserve, schools & the Coburg Market. Inspections are sure to impress!

Description:
Classic Charm and Contemporary Flair with Room to Move!
Set on a surprisingly deep block of land, this quintessential double-front Victorian (c1899) combines period character with twenty-first century style to deliver a ready-to-enjoy family environment of quality and convenience - all in one of Coburg's premier pockets. Beyond the picket-fenced garden and captivating facade, discover a charming interior comprising three genuinely large bedrooms, dedicated study area and stylish bathroom complete with double vanity, freestanding bath and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Adding to its family credentials is a wide central lounge leading through to the open-plan living and dining areas complemented by a contemporary kitchen with breakfast bar, tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other stand-out features of the period prize include a family-sized laundry, ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, original open fireplaces, high ornate ceilings and solid timber floors. Bi-folds reveal a fabulous outdoor entertaining deck and expansive north-facing backyard garden, plus a large garage/workshop accessed via the rear ROW. Exceptional urban convenience on the edge of Brunswick, it's walking distance to Moreland Station and a choice of tram lines, primary and secondary schools, Merri Creek trails and parkland, as well as easy access to Sydney Road/Lygon Street eateries and renowned retail precincts.

Description:
Inner-Urban Family Perfection
Surrounded by other quality homes in a family-focused Coburg neighbourhood, this distinctive double-storey residence provides a ready-to-enjoy environment of quality and style with its versatile floorplan, impressive features and fabulous living/entertaining spaces. Generously-proportioned rooms and an abundance of natural light, the home's inviting interior boasts three genuinely large bedrooms (master with WIR and private outdoor retreat), home office/potential fourth bedroom, stylish ensuite and main family bathroom along with a guest powder room (third WC) - all with marble-top vanities. Add to this wonderfully spacious open-plan living/dining area with integrated entertainment cabinetry, granite-bench kitchen with Asko dishwasher, plus the benefit of a family-sized laundry and under-stair storeroom. Step outside to discover a sensational al-fresco style entertaining area with built-in water feature and cafe blinds for all-seasons enjoyment, plus a private backyard garden and purpose-built workshop/storeroom. Other highlights of this remarkable home include ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, high ceilings, solid hardwood floors, plus a 4000L watertank, irrigated front garden, solar power and heat pump hot water service, double garage (r/c) with internal entry. Walking distance to Brosnan Community Park and Merri Creek trails, childcare centre, Coburg Lake and swimming pool, it's also close to Coburg High School as well as easy access to Coburg Station, Sydney Road trams, cafes and cosmopolitan shopping precinct. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
First Time Offered Since 1929...
Enjoyed by generations of the one family for the past 90 years, this Californian classic provides a lifestyle of immediate comfort and outstanding inner-urban convenience along with a myriad of options to enhance and expand in the future (STCA). Beyond the distinctive triple-gabled facade, discover an immaculately-maintained interior comprising two large bedrooms with a third bedroom/ study, a central bathroom, separate powder room and additional shower room. Adding to its family credentials is a spacious central lounge, updated kitchen/meals with stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher, as well as a light-filled rear sunroom. Other features of this pristine home include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, high ornate ceilings, internal laundry, plus a sunny backyard with established gardens and extensive brick paving, handy storage shed and side driveway for off-street parking. A short stroll to Melville Road trams, local buses, Coburg West and St Fidelis primary schools, it's also close to Coburg Station, Sydney Road eateries and cosmopolitan shopping precinct as well as easy access to Citylink.

Description:
Renovation Perfection for Picture-Perfect Living
Surrounded by lush landscaped gardens, this captivating Californian provides an absolutely idyllic inner-urban lifestyle with its extended two-storey design, premium inclusions and fabulous living/entertaining spaces both inside and out. Bathed in natural light and immaculate from start to finish, the home's flawless interior showcases three bedrooms (large downstairs master with its own dressing room) and home office/retreat, two full bathrooms (one on each level) and separate powder room. Add to this an elegant lounge with gas-log fireplace, open-design dining area and superb modern stone-bench kitchen with soft-close cabinetry, walk-in pantry, quality cooking appliances and double dishwasher. Other stand-out features include high ornate ceilings and Spotted Gum solid timber floors, split-system heating and cooling, built-in wine rack, gorgeous lead-light windows and plantation shutters all-round. Step outside to discover a sensational al-fresco area complete with integrated heaters and cafe blinds for all-seasons entertaining, first-class BBQ kitchen with commercial-grade rangehood, bi-fold servery (from the kitchen), plus a wonderfully private backyard garden including water feature, as well as a versatile studio/storeroom and secure carport (r/c rollerdoor) to ROW. Walking distance to Melville Road trams, local buses, Coburg West and St Fidelis primary schools, it's also close to Coburg Station and shopping precinct as well as easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway. Simply stunning!

Description:
Family Home In A Premier Location
In a premier location, within the pristine surroundings of the Pentridge Village Estate, this free-flowing home delivers a comfortable family environment, complimented by its versatile layout which offers a spacious two-level floorplan, multiple living zones and close proximity to the best Coburg has to offer. Impeccably presented from start to finish, the home's interior showcases a luxurious master suite, equipped with dual WIRs, double vanities and spa ensuite, along with three additional bedrooms (BIRs), dedicated study/office, generous main bathroom and guest powder room (third WC). Offering a formal lounge, spacious upstairs living area leading out to an undercover balcony with park views, plus an expansive open-plan living/dining area accompanied by an open kitchen with a 900mm gas cook top, quality oven and Miele dishwasher. Other stand-out features include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, alarm system, ducted vacuum, solid jarrah hardwood floors, large laundry and under-stair storeroom, plus a sunny backyard with an undercover entertaining area, providing a breadth of atmosphere, along with a internally-accessed double remote garage. Located in the heart of the estate, the home is within close proximity to many facilities, surrounded by the Merri Creek trails, Coburg Lake, Olympic swimming pool, St. Paul's Church and Primary School, Coburg High School as well as easy access to Coburg Station, Sydney Road trams, modern cafes and a renowned shopping precinct.This home must be inspected to appreciate all that it offers for your family. In conjunction with Ian Reid Vendor Advocacy

Extended Elegance with Contemporary Style
Retaining the allure of its Edwardian origins, this freestanding home delivers a lifestyle of quality and versatility with its expanded floorplan, impressive features and immaculate garden surrounds - all in a quiet and convenient family-focused Coburg neighbourhood. Beyond the gorgeous facade, discover an impeccably-presented interior showcasing a wide hallway accessing four spacious bedrooms (all with built-in robes) and stylish central bathroom. The spacious open-plan living/dining area is complemented by a contemporary kitchen complete with stone benchtops/breakfast bar, ample cupboard space, Bosch dishwasher and Smeg cooking appliances (including microwave). High ornate ceilings throughout, this captivating home also includes ducted heating and split-system air conditioning, four working fireplaces (one in each bedroom), solid timber floors, family-sized laundry and large attic storage space (via attic ladder). A short stroll to O'Hea Street buses, Coburg North Primary School and the open spaces of Harmony Park, it's also close to popular Coburg North Village Shopping Centre, as well as easy access Batman Station and Sydney Road trams. Description:
Under Offer! Inspection Cancelled!
Coburg is close to the city (8km from Melbourne) but has the peace and quiet of northern suburbia surrounded by the Merri Creek parkland.
This one-bedroom apartment comes fully furnished with a settled tenant, or you can move in and enjoy the lifestyle yourself. With Tram 59 stations right outside, an awesome cafe right downstairs, and a supermarket opening right behind, love the convenience! Additionally the Coburg Train Station and Sydney Road are both short walks away to offer more abundance of cafes, restaurants, markets, recreational facilities and plenty more.
This special space has open plan living areas with quality fittings including stone bench tops, stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, a spacious bedroom with BIR, bathroom with Euro style laundry, east facing balcony with open views, split system heating & cooling unit and car space.
Currently lease for $400/week on monthly basis.
Pentridge offers something entirely new in 2020, please see this link https://www.shoppingcentrenews.com.au/shopping-centre-news/industry-news/melbournes-iconic-pentridge-transformation-is-underway/
Come and inpsect it before too late!

Description:
Townhouse-Style Apartment with Two Balconies!
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST : Closing Tuesday 3rd December at 5pm
Designed to take full advantage of its elevated position and sweeping north-easterly outlook, this oversized two-level apartment delivers an exceptional low-maintenance lifestyle with its long list of features, dual outdoor areas and easy access to everything that counts. Impressive interior showcases a large upstairs master bedroom with WIR, private ensuite and its own balcony to enjoy the views, second bedroom (BIRs) and main central bathroom. Add to this a wonderfully spacious and light-filled downstairs open living/dining area leading out to a large undercover terrace ideal for relaxing or entertaining. Other highlights include a stone-bench kitchen with breakfast bar and dishwasher, study alcove and full-size laundry, along with split-system heating/cooling and additional panel heaters, plus lift to secure entry foyer, lower-level parking space and large storage cage. Walking distance to Sydney Road trams, endless eateries, boutique shops and major supermarkets, it's also close to Coburg Station, Coburg High School, the delightful environs of Coburg Lake Reserve and endless Merri Creek trails.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Plentiful living space, amazingly generous bedrooms, multiple balconies and mountain views distinguish this naturally bright, three bedroom, three bathroom contemporary residence in popular Pentridge Village. The ground floor features a vast bedroom with ensuite, storage and its own entrance, alternatively suited as an excellent home office. Central level highlights include a big living room and a kitchen/dining with a full complement of stainless steel appliances, and like one of the two huge top level bedrooms they each have a balcony. Two more bathrooms, including a second ensuite, plus a powder room, heating, air conditioning and automatic garage (with direct entry) also feature. Stroll to schools, trams, Coburg Market and City Oval from the compellingly convenient position and its historic setting.

Description:
One of the biggest and brightest in a brilliant locale
With generous proportions throughout, serene surrounds and the ease of single level living, in one of the area's favourite streets, this larger than normal two bedroom ground floor apartment also has a unique bonus of a separate study. Nestled to the rear, of a well-maintained block of only eight, a refreshed layout reveals light filled living room highlighted by floor-to-ceiling windows. Next door is a gas kitchen with meals area, modern benches and cabinetry. Complemented by two double bedrooms with built-in-robes. They share a central bathroom/laundry. Extras include panel heater, modern carpet, ceiling fans, blinds, linen cupboard, secure intercom entry and a car space on title. All within easy reach of schools, shops, cafes, Moreland station, buses, CityLink and John Fawkner Hospital.

Description:
A Glamorous Home Base.
This brand new street frontage three bedroom townhouse featuring an edgy modern façade and bold intelligent interiors makes a glamorous home base. Zoned to Strathmore Secondary College, near buses, Melville Road trams, parks, local shopping, Sydney Road and CityLink, this sophisticated home presents a lifestyle of enviable convenience set amid luxe interiors. Impressive in its sense of space with plenty of natural light throughout, it showcases an indoor/outdoor living domain of exceptional style where Tasmanian Oak floors, an eye-catching floating staircase, dramatic black Smeg/Caesarstone appointed kitchen and Merbau deck and gardens combine to deliver on-trend living. Private bedrooms share two fully tiled bathrooms featuring statement tapware and fixtures while heating/cooling, an alarm, ducted vacuum and garage with remote and internal access will have you in seventh heaven.
